  "prompt": "How can you see if someone deleted you on LINE?",
  "response": "If someone has deleted you on LINE, there are a few signs you might notice:\n\n1. **Profile Picture and Name**: If you can no longer see their profile picture or if it has reverted to the default icon, this could indicate that they have deleted you or set their privacy settings to restrict visibility.\n\n2. **Message Status**: If you try to send a message and it shows as \"Delivered\" but not \"Read,\" it may suggest that they have removed you. However, this isn't definitive, as they might simply have notifications turned off or be ignoring the chat.\n\n3. **Friend List**: If you search for their name in the friend list and cannot find them, it may indicate that they deleted you, but they might have also removed their account or restricted visibility.\n\n4. **Group Chats**: If you were in a group chat with them and they disappear from that chat, it could also mean they have deleted you or left the group.\n\n5. **Add Friend Again**: If you try to add them as a friend and you receive a message indicating that they cannot be added, it could imply that they have deleted you.\n\nKeep in mind that these signs are not foolproof, and the only way to confirm someone's status on LINE may require direct communication with them.",
